<h2 id="guidelines">Guidelines</h2>
<h3 id="title">Loader text</h3>
<p>In most cases the loader should have its own text or be in close proximity to a related message, like a button label. In some cases it's appropriate to have a loader on it's own without a message.</p>
<h3 id="nesting">Nesting</h3>
<p>Loader can be put just about anywhere and will inherit font properties, so when nested in elements like button, anchor, or headings it looks as you would expect it to:</p>
<code-sample>
  <button ord="primary"><m-loader loading hidden></m-loader>Save</button>
  becomes &rarr;
  <button ord="primary"><m-loader loading></m-loader>Saving</button>
  <h2><m-loader loading>Downloading...</m-loader></h2>
  <h3><m-loader loading>Downloading...</m-loader></h3>
  <a href="/cancel-search"><m-loader loading>Cancel</m-loader></a>
</code-sample>

<h3 id="accessibility">Accessibility</h3>
<p>If a Loader doesn't have text it should use
  <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/Accessibility/ARIA/ARIA_Techniques/Using_the_aria-labelledby_attribute" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><code>aria-labelledby</code></a> or <code>aria-label</code>.</p>
